# Antigravity AI Rules — Advanced Playwright Framework

## Quality Gates
Run after every code change — all must pass:

```bash
npm run typecheck                        # Zero TypeScript errors
npm run lint                             # Zero ESLint errors
npm run format:check                     # Prettier formatting check
npx playwright test --grep @smoke        # Smoke suite must be green
```

## Project Structure
- `src/pages/`     — Page Object classes (extend BasePage)
- `src/fixtures/`  — Custom Playwright fixtures
- `src/tests/`     — Spec files with tags
- `src/testdata/`  — JSON · CSV · XLSX · TypeScript types
- `src/utils/`     — Logger · Reporter · Helpers
- `src/config/`    — Environment configuration

## Patterns

### Locators — arrow functions only
```typescript
searchInput = () => this.page.locator('[data-test="search"]');
```

### Tests — must be tagged
```typescript
test('@smoke @P1 Add item to cart', async ({ cartPage }) => { ... });
```

### Logger
```typescript
import { createLogger } from '@utils/logger';
const log = createLogger('InventoryPage');
```

### Imports — use path aliases
```typescript
import { InventoryPage } from '@pages/InventoryPage';
import { test }          from '@fixtures/test-base';
```

## Hard Rules
- No `as any` or `// @ts-ignore`
- No test without a tag
- No locators as plain class properties
- All gates pass before committing
